@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Pathos" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed.

NOTE: I am not sure of this game's 'behaviour' on a stock 68000
      Amiga. For now, until somebody confirms that Pathos runs
      fine on a 68000 machine, this game will require an Amiga with
      a 68020 or faster processor... sorry!

                             How to play?

  To play, click on a tile that is located next to the empty space,
that tile will move toward the empty space. Note that you can use
the cursor keys to move the tiles.

  Each tile has two portions of path; one has an end that starts
from the top and the other end goes to the left (or right). The
other portion of path starts from the left (or right) and goes
downwards. Another type of tile has a portion of path that goes
from the top to the bottom and crosses an other path portion that
goes from left to right.

  When a complete path is created from the entry to the exit, the
path portions are then coloured and the game will count how many
path portions have been used in the completed path...

  You can click on the 'New Game' button anytime to restart the
game...

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

